translated: Hultmark, Åke Sune Georg, clergyman, from Sanda, born on August 8, 1905 in Karlskrona to Bror Sune August H. and Jenny Gustava Lindström. Married in 1937 to Birgit LiHja, who passed away in 1947. They had two children, Birgiitta born in 1938 and Anders born in 1939. He received his degree from the University in 1924 and his degree in theology in 1927. He passed his practical theology exam in 1935 and was ordained in Visby Diocese in 1936. He worked as a primary school teacher in 1924 and 1927. He was a substitute assistant teacher from 1935 to 1936, deputy pastor in Rute from 1936 to 1938, and in Vänge and Sanda from 1938. He became the vicar in Sanda parish in 1939. He was part of Smålands Nation at Uppsala University from 1929 to 1930 and was the chairman of the Sanda, Mästerby and Västergarns parish church meetings since 1939, the Sanda church circle since the same year, and the Västergarns school council since 1940. He was the Crown Ombudsman for the Sanda parish tax assessment since 1940, chairman of the Klinte and Hejde parish tax assessments since 1941, head of the Sanda savings bank since 1939 and treasurer of the same since 1945. He was the chairman of the Sanda municipal council in 1947 and of the forestry association there since the same year. He was awarded FMM Pro benignitate humana.
